webpackJsonp([0x9e31dd49a5cc],{434:function(t,e){t.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:"<p>First day of a new month. It seems to me that while we are adopting agile, we are still very much in a waterfall mindset. I imagine it will take some time to move through this. In any event, the day was spent mostly working on estimates on unknowns far in advance. Something I wonder is how do developments teams trying to work agile quote for departments that expect waterfall? </p>\n<p>The very nature of providing a quote for work to be done, on a system to be built to completion for departments that have set budgets that they have to spend in a set amount of time with expectations of delivery of a highly specified product that looks good in a PowerPoint inevitably leads to waterfall. </p>\n<p>Something to think about...</p>",frontmatter:{title:"One of those days."}}},pathContext:{slug:"/til0038/"}}}});
